For days, Cherington had talked with his White Sox counterpart, Rick Hahn, without being able to narrow the divide between what Hahn wanted for Peavy and what Cherington was willing to give. On Tuesday afternoon, according to a very well-placed source, the White Sox were engaged in serious discussions with the Arizona Diamondbacks, whose general manager, Kevin Towers, had been together with Peavy with the Padres.
